Text: I feel that this week has been our most productive so far.
We had our meeting with Mimi on Tuesday which was filled with a few technical difficulties.
Ruru was unable to join in, due to issues with her Zoom and when I went to show Mimi the current progress my GitHub branch had broken from Yoko committing changes to my branch without realizing.
But we did manage to show our current progress which Mimi was pleased with.
His feedback was mainly that he wanted the UI focused more so the audio files would be the first thing the user would see.
He also wanted there to be a single page per exhibit item, which I thought would be a bit cumbersome.
He also put a fair bit of emphasis on making it easy for them to add more content to the web page after we've finished this project.
I don't think that we really have time to implement a feature that would make it easy but we'll do our best to provide templates and documentation that should make this manageable.

After our mishap with GitHub during that meeting, I spent a bit of time learning how to manage merge conflicts (that's not what caused the issue previously though) as well as get more familiar with some of the terminology.
After I was more comfortable with GitHub I went through it with the team to make sure everyone has sufficient knowledge about how GitHub worked to hopefully avoid the same mistake happening.
We spent time this week, finishing up and tweaking the design and templates for the website.
There were a few issues with the responsive design where elements weren't sitting properly at certain screen sizes.
Also videos weren't being stopped from playing in the background after being closed.
With those issues now sorted, we padded out the content on the pages.

Mimi so far has only provided us with 1 item of content, so we spent a bit of time padding it out using information we found on the internet and using the photos I took from my recent visit to the museum.
Now with the pages filled with content, I've sent them in to their system administrator to be uploaded to their website so we'll be ready for user tested next week.
If the pages don't get uploaded onto the museum domain in time, we'll have them uploaded to Yokos domain in the mean time so we'll still be able to do our user testing.
I'm pretty happy with the progress we've made this week and it's all sort of fallen into place.
All of the pages follow the same templates and design, so this should hopefully make it easy to add more content.
